<HEAD>Exxon Apologizes; Captain Still At Large; Cleanup So Far Futile</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 6th graf to restore dropped word, clarify</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto VDX2, VDX4</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DAVID FOSTER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>VALDEZ, Alaska (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> apologized and promised compensation for causing the nation's biggest oil spill, which on Monday forced <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION> to shut down its $ 12 million herring fishery in Prince <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Sound </PERSON> for the season. <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> state police, meanwhile, said they expected the surrender Tuesday of <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> Hazelwood </PERSON>, the former captain of the tanker that spilled 10.1 million gallons of North Slope crude after it crashed into <LOCATION> Bligh </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Reef </LOCATION> on March 24. `` We have reason to believe he'll present himself'' at the state police barracks in <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Farmingdale </LOCATION>, said state police spokesman Trooper <PERSON> Craig </PERSON> <PERSON> Rubio </PERSON> in a telephone interview Monday evening. An arrest warrant has been issued in <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION> for <LOCATION> Hazelwood </LOCATION>. The <LOCATION> Huntington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.Y. </LOCATION>, resident is accused of misdemeanor charges of operating a ship while under the influence of alcohol, reckless endangerment and negligent discharge of oil. The oil slick has now grown larger than <LOCATION> Rhode </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION>. The state Fish and Game Department announced Monday that the Prince <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Sound </PERSON> herring fishery, which generates $ 12 million in annual revenues, will not open this year. Officials have previously closed the sound's sablefish and shrimp fisheries. More than half the spawning habitat used by Prince <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Sound </PERSON> herring has been fouled, said <PERSON> Dennis </PERSON> <PERSON> Haanpaa </PERSON>, a fisheries biologist with the department. That bodes ill for both the fish and the fishermen, who tend to catch herring near their spawning ground. Altogether, the Prince <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Sound </PERSON> fishing industry is worth more than $ 150 million annually. In full-page advertisements placed in newspapers around the country Monday, <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Lawrence </PERSON> <PERSON> G. </PERSON> <PERSON> Rawl </PERSON> said, `` I want to tell you how sorry I am that this accident took place.'' <PERSON> Rawl </PERSON>'s statement also appeared to respond to harsh criticism from Alaskan officials, fishermen and environmentalists who accuse <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> of reacting slowly and inadequately to the spill. `` We believe that <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> has moved swiftly and competently to minimize the effect this oil will have on the environment, fish and other wildlife,'' he said. <PERSON> Rawl </PERSON> also offered to `` meet our obligations to all those who have suffered damage from the spill.'' Four class action lawsuits already have been filed against <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> at the outset of what could be years of litigation over the accident. In an interview from the company's headquarters in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Raymond </PERSON> said he hopes the `` emotional type of atmosphere'' generated by the spill does not prompt <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> to reject the oil industry's request to drill in protected wildlife areas. However, that could be precisely the outcome of the spill, <ORGANIZATION> Interior </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> Manuel </PERSON> <PERSON> Lujan </PERSON> suggested in a speech to the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ocean </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industries </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>. `` If the image of an uncareful and uncaring industry prevails among the <LOCATI