<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Hernan </PERSON> <PERSON> Buchi </PERSON>, the architect of <LOCATION> Chile </LOCATION>'s successful free-market economy, says he has resigned as finance minister to consider running for president In response to <PERSON> Buchi </PERSON>'s departure, President <PERSON> Augusto </PERSON> <PERSON> Pinochet </PERSON> asked his 15 other Cabinet members Monday to resign so he could reorganize the body. Government spokesman <PERSON> Miguel </PERSON> <PERSON> Angel </PERSON> <PERSON> Poduje </PERSON> said <PERSON> Buchi </PERSON>'s replacement and any other Cabinet changes would be announced on Wednesday No important changes were foreseen in economic policy. <PERSON> Buchi </PERSON>, 40, said he resigned to study the persistent appeals of a group of conservative politicians and business leaders who want him to run for president in the Dec. 14 elections. The group has plastered bumper stickers and posters supporting <PERSON> Buchi </PERSON>'s candidacy throughout the capital and said last week it has collected 142,000 signatures from citizens backing the campaign. `` It never was, and is not, my intention to be presented for this type of candidacy,'' <PERSON> Buchi </PERSON> told reporters at the <ORGANIZATION> Finance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION>. `` Nonetheless, the situation has reached the -LRB- point -RRB- that my name is being publicly mentioned. `` I reached the conclusion that analyzing this situation was incompatible with keeping my post as finance minister,'' he said. The December elections are the first since before <PERSON> Pinochet </PERSON> seized power in a bloody 1973 coup, toppling an elected leftist government. The 73-year-old army commander was obliged to call elections after losing a referendum in October on a proposal to extend his rule to 1997. Although his supporters want him to run, <PERSON> Pinochet </PERSON> insists he will not be a candidate. The constitution bars him from running. <PERSON> Buchi </PERSON>, who