ON> Lima </LOCATION> magazine, <PERSON> Oiga </PERSON>. <PERSON> Caretas </PERSON>, another magazine, said the attack highlighted the insurgency's superiority in manpower and weapons. The government is strapped by <LOCATION> Peru </LOCATION>'s worst economic crisis this century. Inflation is expected to reach 10,000 percent this year. Rumors of military coups have surfaced repeatedly in the past six months. More than 14,000 deaths and $ 10 billion in damage have been attributed to the Shining Path guerrillas since 1980, when the rebels turned from propaganda to violence in their fight for a Marxist state. Uchiza is situated in the heart of <LOCATION> Peru </LOCATION>'s cocaine-producing jungle, where rebels protect drug runners in exchange for weapons and money.
