<DATELINE>TEGUCIGALPA, Honduras (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION> on Tuesday accused <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION> of trying to use a regional peace effort to get rid of the Contra rebels without giving up anything in return. Foreign Minister <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> Lopez </PERSON> <PERSON> Contreras </PERSON> told a news conference <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION>'s leftist Sandinista government refuses to talk to the U.S.-backed rebels. `` <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION> does n't want to solve the political and social crisis in <LOCATION> Central </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>,'' Contreras charged. `` It ... just wants a bilateral accord with <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION> to fix the problem of the Contras.'' Between 10,000 and 11,000 Contra fighters and their families began moving into Honduran base camps near the border with <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION> last spring after <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> military aid ended and a cease-fire began. <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION>, which announced another of its monthly, unilateral extensions of the cease-fire Tuesday, had no immediate comment on the Honduran charges. <PERSON> Lopez </PERSON> <PERSON> Contreras </PERSON> said `` <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION> should offer internal political conditions that permit the quick return of the Contras, their families and more than 40,000 Nicaraguan refugees that have been in <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION> since 1981.'' <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION> wants the Contras `` to return to <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION> as quickly as possible. But this is the responsibility of the <ORGANIZATION> Sandinistas </ORGANIZATION>, who absolutely refuse to talk with the Contras,'' he said. In February, the presidents of <LOCATION> Nicaragua </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Honduras </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Guatemala </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> El </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Salvador </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Costa </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rica </LOCATION> agreed to come up with a plan by mid-May for disarm