f oil into <LOCATION> Alaska </LOCATION>'s Prince <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Sound </PERSON>. He has been fired. <PERSON> Hazelwood </PERSON>'s parents, <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> and <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON>, who also live in <LOCATION> Huntington </LOCATION>, told police they did not know where their son is. `` There was no deal cut,'' said <PERSON> Fazio </PERSON>. `` We told the family that it would be better for him, down the road, to turn himself in voluntarily.'' If <PERSON> Hazelwood </PERSON>, 42, does not surrender within the next two days police will actively pursue him, <PERSON> Fazio </PERSON> said. `` Right now if we see him on the streets, we will lock him up,'' said <PERSON> Fazio </PERSON>. `` We are anxious to bring him into custody.'' The captain is charged with operating a ship while drunk, reckless endangerment and negligent discharge of oil. The charges, all misdemeanors, carry up to two years and three months in prison and a $ 10,000 fine.
