from interference by government officials. A school official said the university permitted students to take part in activities `` as long as they were healthy and good for the students.'' But, <PERSON> Yan </PERSON> <PERSON> Huajiang </PERSON>, a school spokesman, declined to define what type of activities those included. He said the university would take measures to stop `` unhealthy'' activities. He declined to comment on the poster. According to the poster, since the autumn semester, students have been meeting in `` democratic salons'' to discuss political topics. But recently school officials and authorities from the <LOCATION> Beijing </LOCATION> city government have broken up the meetings, it said.
