<HEAD>Minnesota Will Fight Northwest Takeover Attempt, Officials Say</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARY R. SANDOK</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Gov. <PERSON> Rudy </PERSON> <PERSON> Perpich </PERSON> and other <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION> officials are pursuing a number of options aimed at thwarting a takeover of <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>, a move they see as a threat to the state's economy. `` They're in for one hell of a fight,'' House Speaker <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Vanasek </PERSON> said Monday of two groups that have proposed buying <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION>'s parent company, <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which is based in suburban <LOCATION> Eagan </LOCATION>. Investor <PERSON> Marvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> has offered to buy <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> for $ 2.62 billion, or $ 90 a share. <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> owns 3 percent of <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION>'s 29.1 million shares. A second, unidentified group of investors that owns 4.9 percent of the stock also is interested in buying the company, <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> says. <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> stock closed down 50 cents Monday at $ 84.37 -LCB- a share on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Vanasek </PERSON> was among the legislative leaders and constitutional officers from both political parties, union officials and others who pledged at a news conference to back <PERSON> Perpich </PERSON> in what he has described as an `` all-out war'' against a hostile takeover of the nation's fourth-largest carrier and one of the state's largest employers. <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> has indicated its board will review the <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> offer, which he insists is friendly, but the company has said it intends to remain independent. The airline has not asked for state assistance, state officials have said. But unionized machinists, pilots, and fl